claim.claim-text:
1. A golf ball having improved durability, the golf ball comprising:
a core;
a mantle disposed on the core;
a cover disposed on the core; and
at least one cover layer disposed on the mantle, wherein at least one of the mantle and cover layers comprises a composition comprising a mixture of glass particles and an ionomeric or non-ionomeric material, wherein each of the glass particles is a glass flake with a specific gravity ranging from 2.0 to 3.0, a particle size distribution ranging from 45 microns to 1700 microns, and a thickness ranging from 2 to 7 microns.
